00:02:59.240 --> 00:03:03.830
So question one, if a complex
electromechanical system has

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:07.810
1,850 individual part numbers--
this is at the lowest level--

00:03:07.810 --> 00:03:11.440
how many levels do you expect
the drawing tree to have?

00:03:11.440 --> 00:03:14.230
Everybody provided the
same answer, four, right?

00:03:14.230 --> 00:03:17.170
This is basically a
straight application

00:03:17.170 --> 00:03:20.230
of the magic number seven rule.

00:03:20.230 --> 00:03:27.700
And in practice, not
everybody will go exactly

00:03:27.700 --> 00:03:31.420
for four levels, but
that's the basic idea.

00:03:31.420 --> 00:03:34.750
If you decompose the system with
this human cognitive bandwidth

00:03:34.750 --> 00:03:38.830
in mind, for a system of
that level of complexity,

00:03:38.830 --> 00:03:42.100
you should expect, roughly,
a four layer decomposition.

00:03:42.100 --> 00:03:46.630
So I'm very pleased that
everybody got this answer.

00:03:46.630 --> 00:03:50.830
But with the caveat
that there may

00:03:50.830 --> 00:03:52.660
be deviations from
this rule, and you

00:03:52.660 --> 00:03:56.050
can go for a flatter
tree with fewer levels.

00:03:56.050 --> 00:03:58.840
But you have to be aware
of the implications

00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:00.890
that that may have.

00:04:00.890 --> 00:04:02.560
OK, so that's great.

