00:37:20.130 --> 00:37:23.380
Review, is agree on what
the requirements are,

00:37:23.380 --> 00:37:27.270
what the system should achieve,
but not necessarily how

00:37:27.270 --> 00:37:28.770
that will be achieved.

00:37:28.770 --> 00:37:32.070
And then at CDR, I
would say it's too late.

00:37:32.070 --> 00:37:35.160
The CDR is where you
lay out all the details

00:37:35.160 --> 00:37:38.860
of how the system will be
built, operated, the software.

00:37:38.860 --> 00:37:42.420
So that the high level design,
the concept, the architecture,

00:37:42.420 --> 00:37:46.740
should have been decided and
agreed upon way before the CDR,

00:37:46.740 --> 00:37:49.000
and it's the PDR where
that's happening.

