summarizes the goal.

01:09:18.380 --> 01:09:22.689
So the mission of Octanis I is
to build a reusable autonomous

01:09:22.689 --> 01:09:27.279
solar powered and open source
for outdoors, and in this case,

01:09:27.279 --> 01:09:31.819
for an extreme environment
like Antarctica.

01:09:31.819 --> 01:09:34.420
So let's go down
to V-model, right.

01:09:34.420 --> 01:09:37.370
We'll start with the
stakeholder analysis.

01:09:37.370 --> 01:09:40.430
In our case, it's pretty simple.

01:09:40.430 --> 01:09:44.950
It's the Antarctic
Institute from Ecuador,

01:09:44.950 --> 01:09:48.520
which we contacted and
showed our project,

01:09:48.520 --> 01:09:53.410
and they were pretty happy about
this, and I want to learn more.

01:09:53.410 --> 01:09:54.880
So we presented our project.

01:09:54.880 --> 01:09:57.670
We sent in a proposal
and are right now,

01:09:57.670 --> 01:10:01.410
writing the final
documents for them.

01:10:01.410 --> 01:10:03.400
And what we basically
have to provide

01:10:03.400 --> 01:10:08.980
is just the goals of the mission
and the scientific findings

01:10:08.980 --> 01:10:11.080
we're going to have, so
we will produce a paper

01:10:11.080 --> 01:10:16.630
at the end of this and
write about what we found.

01:10:16.630 --> 01:10:21.160
