rover shall provide 10 watts

01:10:29.950 --> 01:10:35.540
on average, so we
figured that out after

01:10:35.540 --> 01:10:36.940
like riding on a power budget.

01:10:36.940 --> 01:10:42.080
Should We want to drive around
that will cost that much power,

01:10:42.080 --> 01:10:47.260
and that will be that much
time during the day, and so on.

01:10:47.260 --> 01:10:50.656
So that was the number
we came up with.

01:10:50.656 --> 01:10:53.020
Oh, and the interior
temperature shall not

01:10:53.020 --> 01:10:56.890
drop below minus
20 degrees Celsius,

01:10:56.890 --> 01:11:00.400
so about 10 Fahrenheit.

01:11:00.400 --> 01:11:06.160
That's basically the point where
you cannot charge the battery

01:11:06.160 --> 01:11:12.110
any more because of the
chemical composition of it.

01:11:12.110 --> 01:11:13.810
So standard batteries,
you shouldn't

01:11:13.810 --> 01:11:16.270
go below minus 10 degrees.

01:11:16.270 --> 01:11:19.840
That's really a hard
requirement we have to provide.

01:11:19.840 --> 01:11:23.050
The total weight shall
not exceed 2.5 kilograms.

01:11:23.050 --> 01:11:26.770
Basically, we look already for
the mission, for the balloons--

01:11:26.770 --> 01:11:30.730
so it shouldn't be too
expensive to put the helium--

01:11:30.730 --> 01:11:33.010
like, to buy the
helium and so on.

01:11:33.010 --> 01:11:36.480
And the rover shall be
able to communicate to us

01:11:36.480 --> 01:11:38.090
from any point of the Earth.

01:11:38.090 --> 01:11:42.820
For that, they basically
used the Iridium Network,

01:11:42.820 --> 01:11:47.140
which you can pay like
for a text message.

01:11:47.140 --> 01:11:51.250
You can pay something and
you can send your message

01:11:51.250 --> 01:11:52.350
from any point as well.

01:11:52.350 --> 01:11:55.630
There's a bunch of satellites
covering the whole planet

01:11:55.630 --> 01:11:57.850
basically.

01:11:57.850 --> 01:12:02.260
And [INAUDIBLE] managed to climb
the slope, a certain slope.

