We have, actually, more power
output than the small chip,

01:16:59.490 --> 01:17:04.410
and it's basically adaptable
to what we need exactly.

01:17:04.410 --> 01:17:08.370
And we, in the end,
went for the second--

01:17:08.370 --> 01:17:14.100
for the right option mainly
because of the power output

01:17:14.100 --> 01:17:16.000
because the 10 wants imply--

01:17:16.000 --> 01:17:21.330
a few amps, actually, of output
and a solar powered input

01:17:21.330 --> 01:17:22.930
that would have to be managed.

01:17:22.930 --> 01:17:25.200
And that's just not
possible for the small chip

01:17:25.200 --> 01:17:28.080
we had in our first
prototype actually.

01:17:28.080 --> 01:17:31.770
So we had a concept
that was inspired

01:17:31.770 --> 01:17:35.120
from the Swiss [? Cube ?]
Satellite because I remember

01:17:35.120 --> 01:17:38.560
going to work there
for his masterpiece,

01:17:38.560 --> 01:17:42.690
and he got inspired from
his concept of having

01:17:42.690 --> 01:17:47.000
this particular
architecture that implies

01:17:47.000 --> 01:17:49.250
having a shared VSS buss.

01:17:49.250 --> 01:17:54.800
So you had your 3 volts
that was feed [INAUDIBLE]

01:17:54.800 --> 01:17:57.540
to your system, and
directly to that,

01:17:57.540 --> 01:18:00.390
connected to solar
panels and the battery.

