The [INAUDIBLE]
materials-- right now,

01:18:36.460 --> 01:18:38.510
we're programming the framework.

01:18:38.510 --> 01:18:41.400
And testing, that's
also ongoing.

01:18:41.400 --> 01:18:44.820
And at the same time,
optimized for having cheaper

01:18:44.820 --> 01:18:47.570
components-- components
with the smaller footprint,

01:18:47.570 --> 01:18:52.100
so you save space on
your PCB and so on.

01:18:52.100 --> 01:18:55.060
So that would be really at
the bottom of the [INAUDIBLE]

01:18:55.060 --> 01:18:57.370
right now.

01:18:57.370 --> 01:19:01.800
Also, maybe, a good example
that shows this trade space

01:19:01.800 --> 01:19:06.700
exploration would be
the mechanical design.

01:19:06.700 --> 01:19:09.934
So the driving mechanism,
that could be--

01:19:09.934 --> 01:19:11.850
well, wheels like we had
it, but it could also

01:19:11.850 --> 01:19:18.540
be like caterpillar or any
other kind of mechanism.

01:19:18.540 --> 01:19:23.580
The motors could be cheap
ones from eBay for $3 a piece

01:19:23.580 --> 01:19:27.016
or like high end Maxon motors
we all love here in Switzerland,

01:19:27.016 --> 01:19:29.150
right?

01:19:29.150 --> 01:19:33.320
And well, you could
print that with a 3D

01:19:33.320 --> 01:19:35.190
printer, the structure.

01:19:35.190 --> 01:19:37.920
Even the gears, you
can print them out,

01:19:37.920 --> 01:19:39.795
actually, yourself,
with plastic.

01:19:39.795 --> 01:19:41.115
It works actually.

01:19:41.115 --> 01:19:43.350
Or you could select
metallic parts.

01:19:43.350 --> 01:19:44.910
We have also a few--

01:19:44.910 --> 01:19:48.930
like, the worm guy for instance,
we need to take a metallic one.

01:19:52.190 --> 01:19:56.340
In the end, we had a combination
