01:24:01.050 --> 01:24:04.260
instead of making
first concept studies,

01:24:04.260 --> 01:24:06.900
and then select the
best one, and only then

01:24:06.900 --> 01:24:12.750
really go to build
it, and cut metal--

01:24:12.750 --> 01:24:15.360
that's [INAUDIBLE].

01:24:15.360 --> 01:24:18.360
That we can do
because we basically

01:24:18.360 --> 01:24:22.020
have all these low cost
components, so it doesn't cost

01:24:22.020 --> 01:24:25.420
us a lot to build one
prototype because everything

01:24:25.420 --> 01:24:29.000
is 3D printed,
everything is electronics

01:24:29.000 --> 01:24:33.920
that is pretty cheaply
doable right now.

01:24:33.920 --> 01:24:37.930
And yeah, we can do this.

01:24:37.930 --> 01:24:41.760
And to motivate us, or
to give us some pressure,

01:24:41.760 --> 01:24:43.620
we set these
artificial deadlines.

01:24:43.620 --> 01:24:47.320
So we put the design
freezes in our calendar.

01:24:47.320 --> 01:24:49.650
So from this point
on, we will not

01:24:49.650 --> 01:24:52.950
change these parts of
the systems any more.

01:24:52.950 --> 01:24:57.330
That allows us to kind
of move on on this

01:24:57.330 --> 01:25:00.810
and get some things
custom, for granted,

01:25:00.810 --> 01:25:03.720
so we don't have to adapt
other things because something

01:25:03.720 --> 01:25:05.730
else changed again.

01:25:05.730 --> 01:25:08.640
And we have these field
tests like I talked about

01:25:08.640 --> 01:25:11.220
in Sweden and on the
glaciers, so that gives us

01:25:11.220 --> 01:25:12.810
kind of pressure as well.

